						<div class="postbody">Do what loopy said (he made asm6!! Thank you so much loopy!!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> ) and reverse your slashes.  Webpage urls use &quot;/&quot;; but, directory paths use &quot;\&quot;, at least in Windows OS, what we use.<br />(was blessed to figure this out after opening command prompt  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green" /> <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />)<br /><br />Also, my sister created our &quot;nametable&quot; files with <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.db</tt> statements so we must use <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.incsrc</tt> for those. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

