				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The first slash indicates a rooted path.<br /><br />So let's say your project directory was C:\development\myproject\source, and you included /data/something.h.  The first slash turns the path back to C:\, then it looks in C:\data, which fails.<br /><br />You can also put a dot before the slash, that will also fix the path.<br /><br />Forward vs Backslash isn't an issue here, Windows accepts both as long as you aren't at the cmd prompt.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Here come the fortune cookies!  Here come the fortune cookies!  They're wearing paper hats!</div>
